Kiess route monitors have flagged three Ashfang remnant combat roles operating toll-blocking networks on the Cinderteeth foothills approaches — raiders intercepting courier runs, enforcers controlling chokepoints, and trackers hunting anyone who slips past the first screen. Wall Command cannot resume escort scheduling until all three roles are confirmed suppressed. Engage one raider, one enforcer, and one tracker so dispatch can assess whether the withdrawal already ordered is genuine or tactical.
Kiess dispatch has confirmed a genuine tactical withdrawal from the foothills approach zones after your engagement reports came in. Wall Command analysts note the Ashfang remnants have pulled back rather than regrouped, which implies a command structure still directing them from deeper in the range. The postmaster wants field confirmation that the retreat is not a Blood Oath hold-pattern designed to draw patrols inside.
